race.comment: Competitive. RHOOKY (6) didn't have much luck at Ararat first-up and got to within 1.3L of the winner over this trip. He'd impressed over 1700m on debut and in a Flemington Open 3 over 2000m, following that. Has plenty of upside and is well-placed to win. I'LLBETHERE (3) found the line nicely when narrowly beaten over 1411m at Seymour first-up. Had been well-prepared and he's jumped out at Ararat since. Draws the inside gate and the step up to the mile is sure to suit. A threat. BONCAPO (8) finished 1L behind RHOOKY at Ararat off a near miss on debut. He's in the premier stable and is sure to keep improving. Coffey goes aboard today. VALOR BOUND (9) debuts for a sharp stable. Has impressed at the jumpouts and the blinkers are on. Has John Allen booked and he has to be kept verey safe.
